OL,3,CInfected blood scandal: How much
OL,4,Ccompensation will victims receive?
OL,6,FAs a result of the "biggest treatment
OL,7,Fdisaster in NHS history", around 3,000
OL,8,Fpeople have died - among them 380
OL,9,Fchildren. More are dying weekly.
OL,11,FThe 2,527-page report from the
OL,12,FInfected Blood Inquiry, published on
OL,13,FMonday, found the scandal "could
OL,14,Flargely have been avoided", people
OL,15,Fwere knowingly exposed to contaminated
OL,16,Fblood products and there was a
OL,17,F"pervasive" cover-up to hide the truth
OL,18,Ffrom successive governments, medics
OL,19,Fand NHS officials.
